WorkItem.Description:
Please consider adding support for object literal property value shorthand, as per the ES6 proposal: http://wiki.ecmascript.org/doku.php?id=harmony:object_literals#object_literal_property_value_shorthand. This would allow for the following:

```ts
function foo(a: number) {
  var b = 123;
  return { a, b };  // instead of { a: a, b: b };
}
```

This seems like a very simple change to the current parser, would save a lot of unnecessary typing, is in-line with the support already added for object literal property shorthands for functions and getters/setters, and would be forward-leaning towards possible eventual support for object destructuring.
